# Recent changes validation and work update on Trello

Every time some work is started:

- Use the Trello MCP to move any related card to the "Doing" column. Feel free to update any related task card with proper comments to best explain what's going on.
- Then, undertake the required work, adding comments to any related task card that needs them.
- Once done, build the project for both Android and iOS to check that the application is still functional.
- Finally, use the Trello MCP to move any related task card to the "AI-Implemented" column. Feel free to update any related task card with proper comments to best explain what's going on. In this last stage, changed files must be ready to be committed with a descriptive message. 

The user is responsible for making the commit (or commits) and pushing it/them to the remote, and moving the task card to the "Done" column in the Trello board.
